CatDescriptText: Mrs. Lillian Farrell, 7286 Santiago Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 30, 1957, pg. 3 with question: "Does the financial aid, given young married couples by parents, encourage or dissuade the latter's realization of marital responsibilities?" answer reads: "I think that it depends on the individuals. Some whom you give financial aid, it helps, while others who receive money from their parents become trifling."
